Even though the GNU assembler's configure script allows the GNU
assembler to be build on Mac OS X, the binutils' configure script
in the parent directory explicitly disables the GNU assembler on
Mac OS X. This patch removes the lines that disabled the assembler.

diff -u -r binutils-2.24/configure binutils-2.24-patched/configure
--- binutils-2.24/configure	2013-11-08 02:13:48.000000000 -0800
+++ binutils-2.24-patched/configure	2016-05-06 17:27:36.713444311 -0700
@@ -3570,11 +3570,11 @@
     noconfigdirs="$noconfigdirs sim target-rda"
     ;;
   x86_64-*-darwin[912]*)
-    noconfigdirs="$noconfigdirs ld gas gprof"
+    noconfigdirs="$noconfigdirs ld gprof"
     noconfigdirs="$noconfigdirs sim target-rda"
     ;;
   *-*-darwin*)
-    noconfigdirs="$noconfigdirs ld gas gdb gprof"
+    noconfigdirs="$noconfigdirs ld gdb gprof"
     noconfigdirs="$noconfigdirs sim target-rda"
     ;;
   *-*-dragonfly*)
